comment: Matthews (DAL) does not establish a legal guarding position prior to the contact with Augustin (DEN) on the pass and crash play.
Matthews (DAL) and Barton (DEN) make incidental contact with one another away from the ball.
Arthur (DEN) makes contact with Matthews' (DAL) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Nowitzki (DAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Felton (DAL) and Faried (DEN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Faried (DEN) sets the screen and gives Felton (DAL) room to avoid the contact. Faried retreats at the time of the contact and absorbs it.
Felton (DAL) legally contests Barton (DEN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Felton (DAL) makes incidental contact with Barton (DAL) away from the ball.
Arthur (DEN) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Parsons (DAL) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Williams (DAL) and Augustin (DEN) make incidental leg to leg contact.
Augustin (DEN) has part of his hand under the ball when he brings it to a pause and continues his dribble.
Parsons (DAL) maintains legal guarding position and is retreating as he absorbs the contact from Barton (DEN).
Arthur (DEN) makes contact with Nowitzki (DAL) that affects his FOM away from the ball.
Arthur (DEN) makes incidental contact with Nowitzki (DAL), who then makes incidental foot to foot contact with Augustin (DEN) that causes him to fall to the floor.
Barton (DEN) makes contact with the ball after it hits the backboard.
Faried (DEN) sets the screen on Felton (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Following the screen, Felton (DAL) grabs and holds Faried (DEN) affecting his FOM away from the ball.
Nowitzki (DAL) makes contact with Faried's (DEN) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Harris (DEN) makes incidental contact with Parsons (DAL) that does not affect his FOM or ability to catch the pass.
Nowitzki (DAL) pushes Barton (DEN) from behind and causes him to make contact with Felton (DAL) that affects his RSBQ.
Barton (DEN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Felton's (DAL) driving layup attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by Felton.
Matthews (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Barton (DEN). Any contact by Matthews is incidental and does not affect Barton's RSBQ.
[Observable in enhanced video] Arthur (DEN) moves his pivot foot.
Nowitzki (DAL) sets the screen on Barton (DEN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Nowitzki (DAL) makes a normal basketball move as he spins toward the basket.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was conclusive video evidence that showed that Williams (DAL) was the last player to touch the ball prior to it going OOB. The ruling on the court was overturned and Denver was awarded possession.
Faried (DEN) sets the screen on Harris (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Parsons (DAL) legally contests Barton's (DEN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Nowitzki (DAL) makes contact with Faried's (DAL) arm and body that affects his layup attempt.
Williams (DAL) legally contests Barton (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Nowitzki (DAL) secures the rebound and Harris (DEN) does not obtain a legal guarding position at the time of the contact.
Faried (DEN) commits a take foul on Williams (DAL).
Miller (DEN) commits a take foul on Barea (DAL).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the field goal attempt by Miller (DEN) occurred after the clock expired was confirmed.
